condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :PAD Annex 4 Paragraph 38 | Description :All transactions pertaining to the NIMF shall be subject to a separateannual audit by COA. A separate audit certificate shall be issued by COA. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PAD Annex 7 Table 1 Internal Controls | Description :Implementation of the action plan adopted & implemented byNIA to address COA findings on non-compliance with internal controls& accounting policies. Resolution of significant issues by2010.| Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PAD C.6 | Description :Annual independent validation report on the severance payments shall be submitted to theBank, in scope and detail, and under termsof reference acceptable to the Bank. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PAD C.6 | Description :Copy of the internal audit report shall be submitted to the Bank in scope and detail andunder Terms of Reference acceptable to theBank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PAD C.6 | Description :Project Reports will be prepared to monitor and evaluate the progress of the Project onthe basis of the monitoring indicators set forth in Annex 3, each one covering the period of one calendar sem. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PAD C.6 | Description :The Borrower shall allocate to the National Irrigation Management Fund (NIMF) every yearthe cash equivalent of at least the actualpersonnel savings due to the NIA Rationalization Plan implementation | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PAD C.6 | Description :The Borrower shall have its FS audited in accordance with the provisions of Sec. 5.09(b)of the General Conditions. Each audit of the FS shall cover the period of one FY of the Borrower. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PAD C.6 | Description :The project shall maintain an adequate financial management system in accordance withSection 5.0 of the General Conditions | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PAD C.6 | Description :Unaudited Interim Financial Reports (IFRs) will be submitted to the Bank, in form andsubstance satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :Quarterly
